The itermonthdates() method

      which requires specifying the year and month.As a result, all days in the specified month and year are returned, as well as all days before the beginning of the month or the end of the
      month that are necessary to get a complete week.
****************************************************************  
import calendar  

c = calendar.Calendar()

for date in c.itermonthdates(2019, 11):
    print(date, end=" ")


